The ANC in KwaZulu Natal has resolved to remove eThekwini Mayor Zandile Gumede from her position. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The ANC in KwaZulu-Natal announced the axing of eThekwini mayor, Zandile Gumede. The Provincial Executive Committee also resolved to "redeploy" all exco members serving in the eThekwini municipality and Msunduzi municipality. WATCH: ANC KZN announces resolution on eThekwini mayor “All ANC members that are servicing as Exco members in eThekweni and uMsunduzi must be redeployed, ” said ANC provincial secretary Mdumiseni Ntuli. Gumede is facing fraud and corruption charges relating to a R208-million waste tender. She is out on R50,000 bail and is due back in court in January next year.